            US returns looted bells to Philippines after 117 years
            Three bells looted by US troops more than a century ago have been returned to their church in the Philippines.President Rodrigo Duterte praised his countrymen and the US at a ceremony in Balangiga, where the treasures were taken 117 years ago.The bronze bells were seized during the Philippine-American War as part of reprisals following a massacre.In August, the US Embassy announced the return of the so-called Balangiga bells after decades of pressure.
                
                        15 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
